metadata.name: Observance #181
metadata.description:
Happy birthday fxhash!

Observance is a collection of 365 pieces, one to mark each day of fxhash's first year.

4 seasons
7 days
12 months
365 dates

Each piece has an alternate birthday palette & all pieces can be saved as an SVG for plotting

Hit 'p' in live mode to save a 3720‚Ää√ó‚Ää5262px PNG
Hit 's' in live mode to save a plottable SVG

This is a generative NFT work by aotearoan, 2022

50% of proceeds go to support Processing.org

metadata.name: Secret Garden #27
metadata.description:
Secret Garden

This secret garden, which does not exist anywhere else, is a secret space found in the brain of AI, that is, in the latent space. Would the AI ‚Äã‚Äãthat created these mysterious gardens have memories of the scent of flowers in its brain?
No matter how well a machine imitates the human learning process, it has inherent limitations. Humans remember the situation by comprehensively utilizing the five senses, including not only the visual information of the flowers, but also the melodies that flowed at that moment, the buzzing of flying bees, the dizzying scent of flowers, and the warm sunlight. However, this AI only does fractional numerical calculations using only the given pixel RGB values.

Humans with much more complex brains and computational systems are passionate about the images that AI creates. However, if you think about it a little, it seems that this interest may be a kind of leisurely relaxation for mature beings to watch the development of immature beings.
This AI doesn't even know what it just built.


* Draw algorithmic strokes by reference the color of AI-generated flower garden.
* One of 832 AI-generated seed images are randomly selected.
* No property(traits), no rarity

[Left click on the screen] : add strokes (Temporarily retouching)
[S] Save to file

Made with Love & P5.js & P5.beizer !
NFT License 2.0
By CSLIM, 2022

metadata.name: Mini Dahlias #235
metadata.description:
Welcome to the enchanting world of "Mini Dahlias" - a mesmerizing generative art project that will spark joy in your heart! Unleashing the magic of algorithms, each miniature masterpiece blooms with vibrant colors and whimsical patterns, transporting you to a dreamy realm of creativity.

But wait, there's more to this fantastical journey! Nestled within each digital artwork lies a hidden treasure - an embedded blueprint that holds the secret to crafting a tangible, real-life edition. Picture it: delicate petals brought to life in the physical realm, ready to be gifted or cherished!

Twenty exquisite physical editions of ‚Äúmini Dahlias,‚Äù crafted with love are destined to be gifted by a friend of mine to random strangers at Burning Man, where creativity knows no bounds!

Inspired by spreading joy and creativity, "Mini Dahlias" is available on fxhash, ensuring that this delightful experience can be enjoyed by art enthusiasts worldwide. Embrace the charm, share the magic, and let the artistry of algorithms paint smiles across the universe. Happy creating and sharing the wonder! üé®‚ú®

metadata.name: Kink #41
metadata.description:
Kink is a representation of the idea that creative evolution is born from the subtle twists, turns, and kinks. 

A base element is manipulated, bent and reshaped, subjecting it to the artistic equivalent of a kink. When several such ideas converge, they give birth to a fresh concept altogether through an evolution in thought and form.

Implemented in JS, this code utilizes the Perlin.js and Simple-noise.js libraries.

Press p to save a PNG of the image in full screen. Press s to save a single complete SVG file for plotting.

And this is a redeemable project in case you‚Äôd like to receive a physical plot!

Pixel Love!

metadata.name: Rebug #183
metadata.description:
A debug view of the underlying particulate algorithm of Atoms' Gaze and Quantum Folly. Refined as a gift for collectors.

Enjoy watching the structures form. Once it's fully rendered you can download a full resolution image of 3508 x 4961 px by ***double clicking/tapping***. At this size the piece is printable at A3 size at 300 dpi. If you're interested in acquiring a signed print please contact @KRANKARTA.

Created on Chrome desktop 103.0 on 2022-08-06 in javascript and GLSL. Results on other browsers/devices may vary.

metadata.description:
Â±±Ê∞¥, literally mountain and water, i.e. landscape. Instead ink, brush, and rice paper, rectangles, p5js and screen, explores not code realism, but code-ism composition and form. Áï´, painting, each landscape is performed, unknowing the exact, as is Chinese landscape painting, the painter, paints his or her fictional landscape. Here my code and the hash paints each landscape with a constrained brush, that is rectangles. 

An important aesthetic factor in Chinese landscape painting is the negative space. Here the positive-negative relation is akin to ying-yang, that in Tai-Chi (Â§™Ê•µ), there are no absolute positive-yang and absolute negative-ying. At the edge of one polar extreme, signals the change towards the other. Like midday, the sun will set. And between midday and midnight, there is plenty of grey. 

I am sorry ‚Äúlife has no scores‚Äù will not be my final drop just yet. Precisely since life has no fixed scores to follow. In preparation for my solo ink show in march, I look towards generative art to give me inspiration. Instead of code imitating brush, my brush and mind aims to discover my own fictional landscapes through code and hashes. 

To see mountains, where there are not any, just the concept of them. I hope you enjoy the mountain view as I will. fxhash is more than a community, when our path crosses, we create art together.  

Press ‚Äò2‚Äô to save png.

Tested on chrome, preview images might be compressed.

metadata.name: Cosmic Poems #120
metadata.description:
Cosmic Poems is the fourth iteration of my work that explores the algorithmic space of typography. In this new piece, I expand on my initial inspirations of the early concrete poetry movement bringing in texts of my own. These short texts are taken from my extensive notes on the subject of artificial intelligence. Snippets of plausible pistes of reflection as well as lighter more tongue in cheek ideas make up the selection I have curated for the work. I hope that it may engage your attention with pleasure.

metadata.name: fx(mash) #167
metadata.description:
fx(mash) is my humble contribution to celebrating #fxhashturnsone

This series is based on a simple algorithm - lines of a random length are drawn on a square grid until the grid is full.

I have added a variety of features based on some of my favorite fxhash projects and a few special guests.

This collection is intentionally diverse and disorderly, that's a nice way of saying I only had a short period of time following the release of Acequia. As a result, some of the outputs might be weird, messy, or even bordering on broken (if you get one of the latter please let me know and I'll reimburse you).

Despite being a bit rough around the edges, I hope fx(mash) reflects some measure of my love for the fxhash community. If you're feeling kind, then perhaps it even harks back to the experimental early days :)

The last year has been an incredible journey, thank you for letting me be a part of our story so far.

Controls (in live view):

- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [g] to toggle grain
- Press [h] for a high-res output

Beta Controls (in live view, definitely not fully tested):

- Press [p] to start/pause animation
- Press [i] to slow down animation
- Press [o] to speed up animation

All primary sales go to Savepakistan.


Acknowledgements:

fx(mash) uses Gorilla Sun's grain implementation, a big thanks to him and meezwhite for a great article that is well worth supporting https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/all-about-that-grain
